51.6	Participatory_budgeting	Participatory budgeting	The first full participatory budgeting process was developed in the city of Porto Alegre, Brazil, starting in 1989. Participatory budgeting was part of a number of innovative reform programs started in 1989 to overcome severe inequality in living standards amongst city residents. One third of the cityâ€™s residents lived in isolated slums at the city outskirts, lacking access to public amenities (water, sanitation, health care facilities, and schools).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/aa/Esquina_democr%C3%A1tica.jpg/220px-Esquina_democr%C3%A1tica.jpg
